===Proper noun===
'''[[le#French|Le]] [[havre|Havre]]''' 
# A city on the north coast of [[Normandy]], [[France]]

====Usage note====
Since "Le Havre" begins with "Le", a [[definite article]], it follows the same rules as the lowercase "le", i.e. if you were to say "I am from Le Havre", it would be "Je viens du Havre", [[du#French|du]] being a contraction of [[de#French|de]] and [[le#French|le]]; or if you were to say "I am going to go to Le Havre", similarly it would be "Je vais aller au Havre". The same rule applies for other towns, for example [[Le Mans]]. Curiously, The "de + le = du" and "à + le = au" rules don't applies to surnames, so you say "Les politiques de le Pen" as opposed to "Les politiques du Pen".